<HEADLINE> Thai Legislators Urge Peaceful Solution to Gulf Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The Thai parliament Wednesday
released a letter calling for peaceful solution to the current
Gulf crisis.
</P>
<P>
The letter was written by 10 current and former legislators to
United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
They urged Annan, who plans to visit Baghdad on Friday, to use
his "power and influence to engage the parties in (the) conflict"
for a peaceful end to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
"We strongly believe that the present crisis can be averted by
peaceful dialogues and diplomatic solution," the letter said.
</P>
<P>
The legislators said the use of force will have "repercussion
on the peoples in other regions, particularly in Southeast Asia."
</P>
<P>
"The use of violent means in solving the crisis will benefit no
one," they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
