<HEADLINE> One More Heroin Refinery Destroyed in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 18 (Xinhua) -- A Myanmar army patrol seized a
mobile heroin refinery recently in northeast Shan State, an
official information release said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The army patrol encountered drug traffickers and engaged in a
shoot-out near Mong-Yu village in Muse township on February 11.
</P>
<P>
From the mobile refinery, 1,005 kilograms of opium and 6.3
kilograms of heroin were seized, the release added.
</P>
<P>
Official reports said the authorities had seized 36 heroin
refineries in Shan State since the beginning of 1997.  
