<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos Says Philippine Banking System Sound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 18 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos Wednesday
said the Philippine banking system is on a stable and sound
footing despite the failure of a second bank.
</P>
<P>
During his regular weekly press conference held at the
Presidential Palace, Ramos said that the rehabilitation package
being drawn up by the Central Bank for Orient Bank is "for the
best interest of the depositors."
</P>
<P>
Orient Bank is the second local bank which went bankrupt amid
the Asian currency crisis.
</P>
<P>
The rescue package for Orient Bank, like that for Monte de
Piedad a few months ago, is for the protection of depositors and
this should be at the least cost to the government, Ramos said.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that three local banks have expressed their
interest in buying Orient Bank.  
</P>
</TEXT>
