<HEADLINE> Malaysia Opposes Military Strike on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Foreign
Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said Wednesday Malaysia remained
opposed to any military strike on Iraq as such action would not
achieve its stated objective and urged Iraq to fully comply and
implement all relevant U.N. Security Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
There is an ever present danger that should a strike takes
place, it might unleash unparalleled environmental damage that was
difficult to anticipate and it might also impinge on the overall
political and security equilibrium, he said in a statement read at
a news conference here.
</P>
<P>
"Malaysia wishes to reiterate that diplomacy is the only option
that is realistic and no other action should be
contemplated...there is a need for continuous and concerted effort
to find a diplomatic solution," he said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia wholeheartedly welcomes the impending visit of United
Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan to Baghdad and attaches great
importance to the visit, he said.  
