<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier on Sino-Russian, Sino-American Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese-Russian and
Chinese-American strategic partnerships have common grounds,
visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier made the comment during a joint interview
with Russian TV, the Independent Newspaper and the Interfax news
agency.
</P>
<P>
Li, who arrived here Tuesday for a two-day official and
good-will visit to Russia following his visits to Luxembourg and
the Netherlands, said that a 21st-century-oriented strategic
partnership based on mutual equality and trust has already been
achieved between China and Russia. Joint efforts will also be made
by China and the United States to build a constructive, strategic
partnership between their two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Such partnerships, the premier said, are aimed at promoting the
healthy and stable development of the Sino-Russian and
Sino-American relations in order to play constructive roles in
keeping world peace and in promoting the progress of all peoples.
</P>
<P>
The partnerships follow the non-alliance, non-confrontational
principles, and are not aimed at third parties, Li added.
</P>
<P>
Because all countries have different situations, geographical
locations and historical backgrounds, the Sino-Russian and
Sino-American relations will not be completely alike, Li said.
</P>
<P>
To illustrate, Li pointed out that China is the largest
developing country in the world, while the U.S. is the largest
developed nation, and Russia shares a 4,000-kilometer border with
China.
</P>
<P>
Given these facts, the premier concluded, the emphases in the
cooperations and the contents of bilateral relations will differ
between the Sino-Russian and Sino-American relations.
</P>
<P>
Since its establishment, the Sino-Russian strategic partnership
has become more substantial in content, Li said.
</P>
<P>
It has been proven that strengthening the partnership conforms
to the long-term basic interests of the two countries, and will
help quicken the realization of a multi-polar world. It is also
beneficial in maintaining world peace and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
It is not an expedient measure that China maintains a
strategic, cooperative partnership with Russia, Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980219.0023 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WHO Announces Influenza Vaccine Formula for 1998/1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Health experts have recommended
influenza vaccine formula for 1998/1999 with changes of two of the
three influenza vaccine components for the previous year,
according to a press release of the World Health Organization
(WHO) here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
As a result of a meeting of international experts, it is
recommended that vaccines to be used in the season 1998-1999
contain: an A/Sydney/5/95(H3N2)-like virus; an
A/Beijing/262/95(H1N1)-like virus; and a B/Beijing/184/93-like
virus.
</P>
<P>
This year's vaccine composition differs from last year's in
that the A/Sydney/5/95(H3N2)-like and A/Beijing/262/95(H1N1)-like
virus strains replace the A/Wuhan/359/95(H3N2)-like and
A/Bayern/7/95(H1N1)-like virus strains.
</P>
<P>
As in previous years, the specific viruses used in vaccine
manufacturing in each country will need to be approved by the
national control authorities.
</P>
<P>
Between October 1997 and February 1998, influenza was reported
in Africa, the Americas, Asia, Europe and Oceania. During the
first three months of this period, outbreaks continued to be
reported in a few countries in the northern hemisphere while
outbreaks continued to be reported in a few countries in the
southern hemisphere.
</P>
<P>
In January 1998, North America and some countries in Asia had
widespread activity while in Europe influenza increased from early
February. Influenza A viruses were predominantly of the A(H3n2)
subtype. In some countries, influenza A(H1N1) viruses were also
frequently isolated.
</P>
<P>
Few laboratory confirmed cases of influenza B have been
reported. Following the first case of human influenza A(H5N1) in
May 1997, 17 additional cases occurred in November and December in
Hong Kong, Special Administrative Region of China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
