<HEADLINE> China, Russia Issue Joint Communique (Part One) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 18 (Xinhua) -- China and Russia issued a joint
communique following a two-day official good-will visit by Chinese
Premier Li Peng here Wednesday. The full text of the joint
communique reads as follows:
</P>
<P>
State Council Premier Li Peng of the People's Republic of China
paid an official good-will visit to the Russian Federation on
February 17-18, 1998, at the invitation of Prime Minister Viktor
Stepanovichn Chernomyrdin of the Russian Federation. The premiers
of the two countries held a third regular meeting.
</P>
<P>
During Premier Li Peng's meeting with Russian President Boris
Yeltsin and talks with Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, the two
sides exchanged views, extensively and intensively, on bilateral
relations and major international issues.
</P>
<P>
The two sides state with satisfaction that the continued smooth
advance of the Sino-Russian partnership of equality and mutual
trust is in line with the interests of the Chinese and Russian
peoples, and is for the good of peace and security of Asia and the
world; and meetings and contacts by leaders of the two nations
have a significant bearing in this regard. The two sides hold the
belief that the first informal meeting between President Jiang
Zemin of the People's Republic of China and President Boris
Yeltsin of the Russian Federation in the second half of 1998 will
further push forward the Sino-Russian strategic partnership of
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two sides express grave concerns over the situation in
Iraq. The Chinese and Russian leaders appeal to Iraqi leaders for
full compliance with United Nations Security Council
resolutions. And advocating a political solution, China and Russia
believe that resort to use of military forces will be of no help
to an effective resolution to the dispute, and will be against the
respective interests of all nations involved. The two sides
identify the needs to pursue a political solution to the current
crisis through further diplomatic efforts, and appeal to all
parties to adopt an attitude of self-restraint and flexibility, so
as to avoid the further deterioration of the situation. China
appreciates the active diplomatic maneuvers by Russia in search of
an peaceful ending to the conflict, and Russia values highly the
related constructive efforts by China.
</P>
<P>
The two sides point out that the Sino-Russian joint communique
on the multi-polarization of the world and the establishment of a
new world order, and the agreement signed by China with Russia,
Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan on disarmament along border
areas have had a positive influence on the world. And as permanent
members of the United Nations Security Council, China and Russia
have constantly enhanced their constructive cooperation and mutual
trust in handling international affairs, which will help promote
the healthy development of the world situation.
</P>
<P>
As two big powers in the Asia-Pacific region, China and Russia
are deepening their bilateral cooperation to consolidate peace and
stability in the region. The two sides, in hope that the Korean
Peninsula maintain long-lasting peace, pledge to continue working
for that end.
</P>
<P>
Both China and Russia attach great importance to creating
conditions favorable for the economic growth of the Asia-Pacific
region. The two sides are willing to keep close bilateral and
multilateral contacts in this aspect.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reiterate that the Sino-Russian strategic
partnership of cooperation is not directed at any third party.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese and Russian leaders emphasized that the expansion
of cooperation in economy and trade has played a pivotal role in
the bilateral relations. The two sides point out with satisfaction
that recent achievements in this area are as follows:
</P>
</TEXT>
