<DOCNO> XIE19980219.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Vows to Fight Environmental Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has vowed to
wage a war against environmental problems, said Benjamin Mkapa,
Tanzanian president and national chairman of the ruling party
CCM.
</P>
<P>
The war against environmental destruction should start from
every household, Mkapa said Tuesday when opening a two-day
seminar for members of the CCM national executive committee.
</P>
<P>
"People must realize that their survival depend on the
nature," Mkapa was quoted by Daily News as saying.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that in 1970s, Tanzania initiated several programs
but the country still witnesses massive environmental
destruction.
</P>
<P>
It is regrettable that the country's environment is worsening
at a very fast rate, he said.
</P>
<P>
As a ruling party, CCM has an obligation to reverse the trend
of environmental destruction and pollution, which was stipulated
in the 1995 election manifesto, he noted.
</P>
<P>
To implement the manifesto, CCM members should take the lead
in using land properly, planting trees and protecting water
resources, Mkapa said.
</P>
<P>
"If every CCM member will plant one tree this year, we will
have three million more trees," he said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that Tanzania, which has 44 million
hectares of forests, is losing between 300,000 and 400,000
hectares per year as a result of tree felling. Only 20,000
hectares of trees are being planted.
</P>
<P>
Between 1979 and 1983, some 17,000 hectares of forests were
destroyed by fire in 66 incidents.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is also expected to review CCM's 20 years of
performance and future direction, the state of the economy and
preparations for parliamentary and presidential elections in the
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the seminar, vice-president Dr Omar Ali Juma said
destruction and pollution of the environment is directly linked
to poverty and if the problem remains unresolved, the nation will
live in absolute poverty.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the CCM leaders should endeavour to educate
on the importance of environmental conservation and protection.
</P>
<P>
Omar cited some of the environmental problems such as the
felling of trees, overgrazing, lack of alternative sources of
energy, as well as polluting of sea. "It is very important to
mobilize people to take part in protecting environment," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said most environmental problems were caused by human
activities. The existing laws were formulated in 1950s and
therefore the penalties are too lenient. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
