<HEADLINE> China, Russia Issue Joint Communique (Part Two) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- The signing on December 29, 1997, of the contract package on
the construction of Lianyungang nuclear power station in Jiangsu
Province, China;
</P>
<P>
-- The active cooperation in the second half of 1997 by China
National Petroleum Corporation and Russian companies in the oil
industry and their signing of several agreements.
</P>
<P>
The two sides highly value the active role played by the
mechanism of regular meetings between Chinese premier and Russian
prime minister in pushing forward the bilateral relations, and are
determined to substantiate the implementation of medium and large
projects of long-term cooperation, so as to bring the bilateral
cooperation in economy and trade to a new high in full match with
the two nations' economic potentials.
</P>
<P>
During Premier Li Peng's visit, the two sides signed documents
as follows:
</P>
<P>
-- The agreement between the government of the People's
Republic of China and the government of the Russian Federation on
cooperation in building high-speed vessels;
</P>
<P>
-- The agreement between the government of the People's
Republic of China and the government of the Russian Federation on
settling inter-government loans and debts;
</P>
<P>
-- The 1998 protocol on the cooperation in economy and trade
between the government of the People's Republic of China and the
government of the Russian Federation;
</P>
<P>
-- The notes to be exchanged between the government of the
People's Republic of China and the government of the Russian
Federation on simplifying the procedures for Russian citizens to
enter the Chinese side of the trade zones along the Sino-Russian
border;
</P>
<P>
-- The notes to be exchanged between the government of the
People's Republic of China and the government of the Russian
Federation on opening a port between the two countries for the
international railway transit of passengers and cargoes.
</P>
<P>
As happened to previous high-level contacts between China and
Russia, the talks and meetings during the current visit by Premier
Li Peng proceeded in an atmosphere of amity, mutual respect and
trust.
</P>
<P>
State Council Premier Li Peng of the People's Republic of China
extended an invitation to Prime Minister Viktor Stepanovichn
Chernomyrdin of the Russian Federation for an official visit to
China, and for the fourth regular meeting between Chinese premier
and Russian prime minister. The Russian side accepted the
invitation and expressed gratitude. 
</P>
</TEXT>
