<HEADLINE> Roundup: Chinese Premier's European Tour Complete Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The official good-will visits
by Chinese Premier Li Peng to Luxembourg, the Netherlands and
Russia from February 12 to 18 have greatly enhanced China's
political and economic ties with the three European countries.
</P>
<P>
The cordial talks between the visiting Chinese premier and top
leaders of the three countries have enhanced mutual understanding
and established common ground. The signing of the China-Russia
Joint Statement and a series of cooperative agreements will have a
remarkable effect on promoting cooperation between China and the
three European nations in a number of fields.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Russia, Li Peng held his third regular
meeting with Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin. They
shared the view that the regularity of premier-level meetings has
played an important role in accelerating bilateral cooperation in
economy and trade, science and technology, transport and nuclear
energy, and in developing bilateral ties. They hope to continue
to give full play to such meetings.
</P>
<P>
The two premiers reached a consensus that through the visits,
the two sides have gained a better understanding of each other's
needs and the areas which offer greater prospects for
cooperation. The meetings have also provided them with the
familiarity and confidence to improve bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two premiers have also confirmed that Chinese President
Jiang Zemin and Russian President Boris Yeltsin will hold their
first non-official meeting in Russia this autumn. The joint
communique issued Wednesday points out that the first non-official
meeting between the two heads of state will help further develop
the China-Russia strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting between Yeltsin and Li Peng, the two leaders
expressed satisfaction over the major achievements made by the two
countries in substantiating and consolidating their strategic
partnership. They agreed to adopt specific measures to further
raise the level of bilateral economic and trade cooperation. They
also agreed that the two countries should continue, as they did in
the past, to maintain contacts and consultations on major
international issues.
</P>
<P>
Li's Russian tour also saw the signing of five documents on
economic and trade cooperation between China and Russia. The tour
is believed to have given a new impetus to the development of
bilateral relations based on mutual respect, equality and trust,
non-alignment and non-confrontation, and were not directed against
other countries.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to the Netherlands, Li Peng held talks with
Dutch Prime Minister Wim Kok, met Dutch parliamentary leaders and
was present at two luncheons held in his honor by Dutch financiers
and entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng and Wim Kok exchanged views on bilateral ties, regional
and international issues of common interest, and reached a
consensus on many issues. Both sides expressed their hope for
better cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The signing of a framework agreement on the next phase of the
4.5-billion-U.S. dollar joint venture petrochemicals complex in
China demonstrated the great potential and prospects for economic
and technological cooperation between China and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Luxembourg, Li Peng held talks with
Luxembourg Prime Minister Jean-Claude Juncker and met Prince Henri
and parliament leader Jean Spautz.
</P>
<P>
Major achievements made during the Luxembourg tour included the
increase of mutual understanding and trust, and the signing of an
annex for scheduled cargo services between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Juncker said at a press briefing with Li Peng that the success
of his visit presented excellent prospects for the development of
relations between Luxembourg and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
