<HEADLINE> African Countries Urged to Make Full Use of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 18 (Xinhua) -- African countries are
urged to develop appropriate national and sub-regional policies
and strategies to address issues pertaining to sustainable use
and management of the natural resources.
</P>
<P>
This was contained in a report adopted by the three-day
technical committee meeting of the 20th United Nations Food and
Agriculture Organization (FAO) regional conference for Africa
which concluded here on Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from 43 member states, 20 of which were represented
at ministerial level, attended the three-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
The report highlighted the linkages between the sustainability
of natural resources, agricultural growth and development, food
security and poverty reduction.
</P>
<P>
A series of follow-up actions have been undertaken at the
national level by African countries after the World Food Summit
held in Rome in November 1996, the report noted, citing
elaboration and adoption of food security strategies for improved
food production and sustainable agricultural growth, and the
revision of national food policies.
</P>
<P>
The report will be presented to the 20th FAO regional
conference for Africa to be held here on Thursday and Friday.
</P>
