<HEADLINE> Commercial Court to Be Set up in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian is in the
process of establishing a commercial court which will deal with
trade and commercial disputes, Chief Justice Francis Nyalali said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nyalali told reporters that the commercial court will be a
division of the high court. At the initial stage, the court will
be manned by three high court judges who will be trained to
handle commercial related cases.
</P>
<P>
The commercial court will operate from the site of the
Kivukoni Magistrate Court, while the activities of Kivukoni court
will move to Kinodoni Primary Court.
</P>
<P>
Nyalali said the commercial court will be equipped with modern
equipment including computers.
</P>
<P>
A commercial court seminar will be held in Dar es Salaam from
Monday to Wednesday, at which experts from both at home and
abroad will give presentations and discuss matters related to the
establishment of the court.
</P>
<P>
Judges at all levels and businessmen will also attend the
seminar, he said.  
</P>
