<HEADLINE> UK in Serious Shortage of Trainee School Teachers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Official figures show that
Britain is in serious shortage of trainee school teachers as the
number of people applying for the course fall sharply, local press
reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the figures, which were leaked to Don
Foster, the Liberal Democrat education spokesman, show that there
are major falls since last year in the number of people applying
for the one-year post-graduate courses which supply the bulk of
secondary school teachers.
</P>
<P>
The number of applicants for the course have fallen by almost
1,000 in the last year and by nearly 4,700 in four years.
</P>
<P>
The 423 applications this year for the course in maths are 22
percent lower over last year and two-thirds down on 1994.
</P>
<P>
The number of chemistry and physics students fall 30.5 percent
and 27.7 percent respectively while English students down 8.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
The figures are much worse than 10 years ago when the then
opposition Labor Party called the problem "alarming", saying
"crisis is not too strong a word to describe the teacher
shortages".
</P>
<P>
The Liberal Democrats said that they will use the figures to
press the government to spend more on education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
