<HEADLINE> Record Bankruptcies Foreseen in Germany This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The number of bankruptcies in Germany
would hit a record high of some 29,000 this year, up from 27,500 in
1997, the Federation of German Cooperative Banks (BVR) forecast
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The increase would occur in the country's construction sector, the
organization noted, while predicting a decline in export-strong
sectors and an overall improvement in the economy.
</P>
<P>
It also projected that investments in the construction sector would
decline by 1.5 percent in western Germany and by 4 percent in the
east.
</P>
<P>
According to the BVR, there would be 20,000 cases of bankruptcies
in western Germany and 9,000 in the east in 1998. 
</P>
