<HEADLINE> Polls: Schroeder Likely to be SPD Chancellor Candidate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Gerhard Schroeder, the Social
Democratic (SPD) head of Lower Saxony state, was likely to win
enough vote in regional elections which would make him the SPD
chancellor candidate for Germany's September general elections,
showed the results of two opinion polls Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In the March 1 state vote, Schroeder needs to obtain vote at
least half a percentage point more than the 44.3 percent he
achieved four years ago so as to win the contest for SPD
chancellor candidacy against SPD leader Oskar Lafontaine, it is
reported.
</P>
<P>
The latest two opinion polls, one conducted by the Infratest
Institute and the other by the Forsa Institute, revealed that
Schroeder would get at least 45.5 percent of the vote in Lower
Saxony.
</P>
<P>
Other recent polls also indicated that compared with
Lafontaine, Schroeder -- regarded as a pro-industry reformer,
would have a far better chance of beating Chancellor Helmut Kohl
in the general elections.
</P>
<P>
Kohl has been in office since 1982. 
</P>
</TEXT>
