<HEADLINE> China Publishes Book on Zhou Enlai in Jiangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, February 19 (Xinhua) -- China released a book on Zhou
Enlai's revolutionary work in the eastern province of Jiangxi,
titled "Zhou Enlai in Jiangxi", here today.
</P>
<P>
The 210,000-character book was complied by historical research
institutes of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Jiangxi
Provincial Committee and Nanchang City Committee.
</P>
<P>
Shu Huiguo, secretary of the CPC Jiangxi Provincial Committee,
said the book reflects Zhou's revolutionary experience and great
achievements and was the best gift the people of Jiangxi
provide for his centennial.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Enlai was born on March 5, 1898, in Huai'an County in
Jiangsu Province, and died on January 8, 1976. He was involved in
many revolutionary activities in Jiangxi from the 1920s to the
1940s, and led the famous "August 1 Uprising" in Nanchang, the
capital of Jiangxi, in 1927, marking the first shot in the fight
against the Kuomintang reactionaries. After the founding of the
People's Republic of China, he made many visits to the province.
</P>
<P>
Zhou served as premier from 1949 to 1976, 
</P>
</TEXT>
