<HEADLINE> Body Of Former Chinese Military Official Cremated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The body of Wang Ping, a
former member of the Standing Committee of China's Central
Military Commission, was cremated in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing, Tian Jiyun and
other senior Party, government and military officials paid a final
tribute to Wang's remains before the cremation.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng, and other state leaders
either went to see him in hospital or sent condolences to his
family after his death.
</P>
<P>
Wang Ping died of illness on Feb.8 at the age of 91. He joined
the Party and the Red Army in 1930 and made many contributions to
China's liberation and was known for his ideological work in the
People's Liberation Army. 
