<HEADLINE> Chinese Soldiers Get Awards For Tibet Resue Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen soldiers of the
People's Liberation Army received awards of first-class and
second-class merit today for their outstanding work during a
recent resue operation in a Tibetan snowstorm.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers and a thousand other servicemen from the Tibet
Military Region, braved harsh weather conditions since September
to clear snow-blocked roads and take relief supplies to victims in
Naqu in northern Tibet.
</P>
<P>
According to military sources, the soldiers cleared 21,000
kilometers of roads and transported 35,50 tons of relief goods to
snow-blocked areas.
</P>
<P>
They distributed 300,000 yuan in cash and 13,000 overcoats and
other clothing to the storm victims and showed discipline during
the resue operation.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony today, Tibet Autonomous Region officials praised
the PLA soldiers as well as the 13 heroes.  
</P>
