<DOCNO> XIE19980219.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Corrupt Enterprise Executives Punished </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Two state-owned enterprise
executives in northwest China's Gansu Province were expelled from
the Communist Party of China (CPC) and removed from their posts
for taking bribes.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made by the Gansu Provincial CPC Commission
for discipline Inspection and the Provincial Department of
Supervision.
</P>
<P>
The judiciary of Gansu Province is looking into their cases
further.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Bingchang, former general manager of the Lanzhou Iron and
Steel Group, was found to have taken more than 800,000 yuan in
cash and treasury bonds as bribes when he served as deputy general
manager of the Jiuquan Iron and Steel Group, up to 1995. He also
abused his power to get another 400,000 yuan in bribes and by
embezzling public funds at Lanzhou Iron and Steel Group.
</P>
<P>
Wei Guangqian, former director of the Liancheng Aluminum
Factory in Lanzhou, was found to have received 520,000 yuan,
130,000 Hong Kong dollars, and 11,000 US dollars in bribes.
</P>
<P>
He was also found to have taken bribes from partners when
the aluminum factory was forming a joint venture with a company in
Guangdong Province, a move that caused the aluminum factory's
property value to drop 279 million yuan, nearly 30 percent of the
factory's total assets.
</P>
<P>
In a circular issued recently, the CPC Central Commission for
Discipline Inspection and the Ministry of Inspection recently said
that the two corrupt officials abused their power and embezzled a
large amount of public funds, causing heavy economic losses and
seriously impairing relations between the Party and the people.
</P>
<P>
The circular noted that discipline inspection departments at
all levels should intensify checks on state-run enterprise leaders
and investigate those who have abused their power for personal
gains or caused substantial loss of state properties by
dereliction of duty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
