<HEADLINE> Farmers Asked to Combat Drought, Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun
today asked farmers to get ready for a fight against drought in
the northern part of China and flooding in the south to make sure
the spring harvest is good.
</P>
<P>
Jiang wrote comments on reports on recent drought and flooding
developments by the Water Resources Ministry, which said that
although there has been rain in northern China, part of the area
is still having dry weather.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in southern China, torrential rains have brought the
flood season well ahead of normal, and record high water levels
have been reported by the Hankou Hydrology Station on the Yangtze
River and the Zhuqi Hydrology Station on the Minjiang
River. Flooding has been reported on the middle and lower reaches
of the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
The National Flood and Drought Prevention Headquarters today
issued a circular to all provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities calling for better preparations against floods and
droughts.  
</P>
