<HEADLINE> Religious Leaders in Somalia Condemn U.S. Threat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Religious leaders in the
Somali capital have strongly condemned the American military
threats against the Iraqi people.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the third anniversary of the Hararyalleh
neighborhood Islamic court Thursday, Somali clergyman Sheikh Ali
Dhere said the American behaviors are provocative and typically
anti-Islamic acts.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Ali Dhere told hundreds of people who gathered for the
occasion that the American leadership will take the
responsibility of the consequences if Iraq is attacked.
</P>
<P>
"The US military build-up in the Gulf means nothing less than
annihilating the Islam in the region," he said, warning that the
U.S. should refrain from what he called "its arrogance and show
of power business in the Gulf."
</P>
<P>
Other religious scholars who spoke at the gathering emphasized
the unity of Islam and the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
The Hararyalleh court has so far fulfilled and solved 1,261
cases of punishment varying from lashes to death sentences, other
penal cases, inheritance, land disputes and others. Thursday's
gathering was also attended by the different sectors of the
community, clan elders, many of Somalia's Islamic movements and
Somalia's Olympic Committee. 
</P>
