<HEADLINE> China Reports Sufficient Farm Production Materials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The production materials for
spring farming, such as fertilizers, pesticides and field
plastics, are in sufficient supply, according to the All-China
Supply and Marketing Cooperatives.
</P>
<P>
The cooperatives forecast the demand for chemical fertilizers
at 160 million tons this year, including 100 million tons for the
spring sowing.
</P>
<P>
Having analysing production and import of chemical fertilizers
and those in stock, the cooperatives said that the country is able
to provide farmers with 186 million tons of chemical fertilizers
this year, and of which, 106 million tons may be available during
the spring farming period.
</P>
<P>
Over-supply last year has kept the prices of these fertilizers
at the level at the end of last year, the cooperatives said,
adding that the current price stands at 1,099 yuan per ton, down
9.8 percent from the same 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Chinese officials have called on departments involved to
prepare enough production materials and funds for the spring
farming.
</P>
<P>
South China, which enjoys a warmer climate and more rainfall
than North China, has led the country in rice planting. Central
and north China areas have also been busy preparing for the spring
farming.
</P>
<P>
China has had good grain harvest for the past three consecutive
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
