<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-one congressmen and five
governors from the Philippine opposition would defect to the
ruling Lakas-NUCD party, the Philippine News Agency reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted Lakas presidential candidate, House Speaker
Jose de Venecia, as saying that the defection would further weaken
the divided opposition and ensure the ruling party's "sweeping
victory in the coming elections."
</P>
