<HEADLINE> Beijing's 13-Year-Old Ambassador For World Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- A 30-meter-long picture of 100
giant pandas painted by a 13-year-old middle school student from
Beijing as a gift for Alexander Lukashenko, president of Belarus,
resulted in an invitation of the student to the Presidential
Palace of Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Yangyang received a letter from President Lukashenko
inviting her to visit Belarus when she sent a picture of a Giant
Panda and a peony with a New Year's card last year.
</P>
<P>
Last week she became the youngest Chinese guest ever at the
Presidential Palace of Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko got to know about Zeng's life in Beijing and
encouraged her to become a master of painting and a little
ambassador of world peace and friendship. She was also given a
young ambassador of world peace and friendship certificate by
Belarus Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries.
</P>
<P>
Zeng learned painting from her father at the age of three and
gave two exhibitions at the cultural center of Belarus and a
children's art school of watercolors, sketches, and traditional
Chinese realistic painting.
</P>
<P>
She was described as talented by local newspapers, and the
State Gallery of Belarus has a painting of hers, "Giant Panda and
Peony."
</P>
<P>
"I never expected that so many little foreign friends like my
paintings. They are very eager to come to China and see real giant
pandas and peony," she said.
</P>
