<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Meets With Hong Kong's Chief Justice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, in a
meeting here today with the Chief Justice of the Hong Kong SAR
Court of Final Appeal, Andrew Li, said that the central
government is satisfied with the work done by the government of
the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
He said that the SAR Court of Final Appeal has been in smooth
operation since its establishment.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Facts show that the 'one country, two systems'
and 'Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong' principle has been
successful."
</P>
<P>
Qian said that maintaining the rule of law in Hong Kong is
vital, and that this is the first time in history that
Hong Kong has enjoyed the right to have a court of final appeals.
</P>
<P>
He also said he thinks a prestigious judicial system will be
established in Hong Kong with the efforts of all involved.
</P>
<P>
Andrew Li said he has had exchanges with his counterparts in
inland areas during his visit to Beijing and it helps increase
ties and cooperation between the judicial sectors in two places.
</P>
<P>
Present at the meeting were Chen Ziying, deputy director of the
State Council's Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office, and Li
Guoguang, vice-president of the Supreme People's Court.  
</P>
</TEXT>
