<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build 3 Billion Sq m of Rural Housing by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- China plans to build three
billion sq m of rural housing by the end of the century to meet
the need of the rural population for better housing.
</P>
<P>
Some five percent of the country's total rural households will
build new houses before the turn of the century, according to a
leading official with the Ministry of Construction.
</P>
<P>
The official said that with the rapid development of the rural
economy, rural residents now hope for better housing, and now the
annual housing projects completed exceeds 600 million sq m.
</P>
<P>
Average per capita housing in rural areas has gone from 17.8 sq
m in 1985 to 22 sq m now, and 100 million houses have been built
in the rural areas over the past five years, with nearly half of
the country's rural households moving or having moved into new
housing, the official added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
