<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Deng Xiaoping Stamps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of philatelists went
out in today's snowfall to buy Deng Xiaoping commemorative stamps
on the first day of issue, the first anniversary of Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
The set of six stamps carry Deng's portrait and pictures of
some important events in his life.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zaixi, a retired policeman, took up position early and
bought the stamps at a downtown post office. He explained: "Deng
Xiaoping led the Chinese people to today's achievements." Zhang
attended a national public security conference some 40 years ago
and still has his group photo taken with Chairman Mao Zedong and
Deng.
</P>
<P>
Six hundred post offices in Beijing carried the stamps,
according to a Beijing postal administration official.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Stamp Corp. also printed first day covers and other
items of interest, and buyers could obtain gold cards
commemorating Deng, which were distributed today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
