<HEADLINE> China (Shenyang)-Italy Trade Fair Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The China (Shenyang)-Italy
economic and Trade Fair, the first non-governmental trade fair in
Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province, was
inaugurated here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Local enterprises provided Italian investors with 22 projects
in the fields of textile, machinery, electronics and garment
processing during the four-day fair.
</P>
<P>
This was a new experiment carried out by the local government
to encourage the non-public sector to conduct economic cooperation
with other countries and regions, said Zhang Shichun, an official
of the Shenyang Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Committee.
</P>
<P>
The city will continue to back such trade fairs to attract
foreign investment, which are sponsored by non-governmental or
individual firms in future, Zhang added.
</P>
<P>
Since China opened up to the outside world, more than 40
countries and regions have built Sino-overseas joint venture
businesses in Shenyang. But the majority of overseas investors
came from the Southeast Asia, Japan and the United States. Only
11 italian-funded businesses were built in Shenyang, bringing in a
direct investment of 6.7 million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
