<HEADLINE> India's CPI-M Raps U.S. Stand on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of India
(Marxist) (CPI-M) Thursday criticized the "brazen and bullying"
stand of the United States toward Iraq.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, the party politburo warned that if
the U.S. proceeded with a military strike against Iraq, it could
lead to an adverse impact on Indo-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
Referring to U.S. President Bill Clinton's speech Wednesday,
the statement said the U.S. has made its intentions clear that it
would bypass the United Nations Security Council and go ahead with
a massive aerial bombardment.
</P>
<P>
The CPI-M asked the Indian government to enhance diplomatic
efforts to check the U.S. action.  
