with Laudrup in London last week before the Italian succeeded
sacked boss Ruud Gullit of Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Bladet Rangers sources had confirming the move would go ahead,
according to the Danish paper Extra.
</P>
<P>
Laudrup has also been linked with moves to Ajax and Manchester
United before. 
