<HEADLINE> Lee Kuan Yew Sits on Advisory Boards: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong disclosed on Thursday that with his agreement, Senior
Minister Lee Kuan Yew presently sits on the international advisory
boards of five organizations.
</P>
<P>
Lee also receives 55,000 US dollars each year as honorarium
from three of the boards, Singapore television reported, adding
that he donates the money to charity.
</P>
<P>
It said Prime Minister Goh disclosed this at Thursday's
Parliament session in reply to a written question by
Non-Constituency-Member-Of-Parliament (NCMP) J.B. Jeyaretnam, who
is leader of the opposition Workers' Party.
</P>
<P>
Goh reportedly said that membership of these Boards gives the
Senior Minister useful insights into the world economy in his
capacity as chairman of the Government of Singapore Investment
Corporation (GIC).
</P>
<P>
The five organizations are: Stanford University Institute for
International Studies; Institute for International Economics,
Washington DC; JP Morgan International Council; Total
International Advisory Board; and Daimler Benz International
Advisory Board.  
</P>
</TEXT>
