<HEADLINE> Daewoo to Increase Exports to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, February 19 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's Daewoo Group has
decided to increase its exports to China to 2.5 billion
U.S. dollars this year, up 15.2 percent over last year, a group
spokesman said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Daewoo, which is the fourth largest conglomerate in South
Korea, will sharply raise shipments of automobile engine-related
parts and other components to China.
</P>
<P>
It has also agreed to provide a total of 90,000 compressors
 to Mudanjiang Air Conditioner Factory in China's Heilongjiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
Daewoo's major export items to China are petrochemical
products, electrical and electronic goods, iron, steel and
textiles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
