<HEADLINE> Pakistani Opposition Launches Anti-Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Jamaat-e-Islami (JI), a
major opposition party in Pakistan, Thursday launched a
country-wide campaign against corruption.
</P>
<P>
The JI, regarded as the third largest political force after
Pakistan People's Party and the ruling Muslim League (N), Thursday
staged its first "accountability caravan," which was attended by
hundreds of people.
</P>
<P>
The campaign is to "create awareness among the masses of the
rising corruption in the country", said JI Chief Qazi Hussain
Ahmed, who led Thursday's caravan from Rawalpindi near Islamabad,
to Lahore, capital of Pakistan's largest Punjab province.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue the caravan in the next three months to
highlight this problem to the people," Qazi told reporters.
</P>
