<HEADLINE> Regional Summit on Burundi to Be Held in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The sixth regional summit on
the conflict in Burundi will take place in Kampala, capital of
Uganda, on Saturday, a State House release said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The summit is a follow-up of the previous one held in
Dar-es-Salaam last September. It will be attended by heads of
state and government from Tanzania, Ethiopia, Kenya, Rwanda, the
Democratic Republic of Congo, Zambia and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Also at the summit will be the facilitator of the Burundi
peace process, Tanzania's former President Julius Nyerere, and
Salim Ahmed Salim, secretary-general of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
The fifth regional summit reaffirmed in its joint communique
that the regional leaders were determined and committed to
promote a negotiated settlement in Burundi and to fully back the
efforts of the facilitator in this direction. It also declared
its preparedness to adopt additional measures to deal with any
obstruction to the negotiation process.
</P>
<P>
According to Hope Kevergere, press secretary to the Ugandan
president, the OAU chief will arrive in Uganda Thursday
afternoon. And Nyerere and Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa are
expected to arrive Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
