<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Hometown Holds Commemorative Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, February 19 (Xinhua) -- About 1,000 of the folks
in Guang'an County, Sichuan Province, Deng Xiaoping's hometown,
gathered at his former residence to remember him today, on the
first anniversary of his death.
</P>
<P>
Tang Lunhui arrived with a board bearing the words "Comrade
Deng Xiaoping's Former Residence" carved in the style of President
Jiang Zemin's handwriting.
</P>
<P>
"It's the most valuable board I've ever made," said Tang, a
locally known woodcarver in Guang'an County, where Deng was born
in August 1904.
</P>
<P>
For a long time, Tang and a group of students gazed at the
board, which was placed in the hall of the residence. They then
visited all the rooms, which are maintained in their original
state and decorated with pictures of Deng in his youth.
</P>
<P>
They also planted several rows of saplings in the courtyard of
Deng's former residence, which is now a national patriotic
education base. 
</P>
</TEXT>
