<HEADLINE> Chinese Remember Two Great Leaders (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Today's People's Daily carried an article by President Jiang
Zemin on the first anniversary of Deng's death, and tonight, CCTV
will carry a prime time documentary, "the Great Monument", in
memory of Deng.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Post and Telecommunications Ministry today issued a
set of six commemorative stamps in memory of the great man, and a
ten-day photo exhibition on his daily life opened. The 112 photos
on display were taken by Deng's eldest daughter, Deng Lin. They
are intended to show the Chinese public another aspect of his
life -- a common father, husband and son.
</P>
<P>
At the recent Beijing Book Fair, books on Zhou Enlai and Deng
Xiaoping's life were some of the best sellers.
</P>
<P>
One Beijing resident said that Zhou Enlai and Deng
Xiaoping "will live in the hearts of the Chinese people for
ever," and that, for the Chinese, they were "ideal state leaders."
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
