<HEADLINE> Macao Newspapers Mark Deng Death Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Some newspapers here Thursday
carried articles commemorating the first anniversary of the death
of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
In a commentary entitled "Forever Commemorate Deng Xiaoping
and Learn From Deng Xiaoping," the Macao Daily News described the
late Chinese leader, who died on February 19, 1997, as a great man
whose great achievements outlive his time.
</P>
<P>
He will continue to be respected and learned from by the
Chinese people, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said Deng's theory has been proved as the only
correct one to guide China in the course of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics and the greatest guarantee for
China's prosperity and reunification.
</P>
<P>
"Deng enjoyed great prestige both at home and abroad and will
be missed, respected and learned from by the Chinese people," said
the commentary.
</P>
<P>
It attributed to Deng Xiaoping's theory Hong Kong's smooth
return to the motherland, the 21st-century blueprint worked out at
 the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
the successful visit by President Jiang Zemin to the United
States last year and other "glorious achievements" made in 1997.
</P>
<P>
"Those remarkable accomplishments are due to the third
generation of China's leadership who has handled domestic and
international affairs by following Deng Xiaoping's theory," it
said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the commentary hailed Deng's concept of "one
country, two systems" as "scientific," saying it has been proved
by Hong Kong's smooth handover and the subsequent prosperity and
stability there.
</P>
<P>
"The correctness of the concept will be further proved by the
prosperity that will follow Macao's handover (in 1999)," the
commentary said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the newspaper Correio Macaense Daily said in a
separate commentary that the best way to commemorate Deng Xiaoping
today is to implement the Basic Law of Macao.
</P>
<P>
"The best action to commemorate Deng Xiaoping is to fully
implement the basic law so that the goal of 'Macao people
governing Macao' and a 'high degree of autonomy' will be
achieved and Macao's prosperity and stability maintained," it
said. "That will also offer a good example for Taiwan in the
course of China's reunification."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
