<HEADLINE> China, Yemen Issue Joint Press Communique (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Talks between Chinese and
Yemeni leaders yielded a wide-ranging consensus on developing
bilateral friendly cooperative relations, and both regional and
international matters of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The joint press communique issued today marked the conclusion
of Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh's five-day state visit to
China.
</P>
<P>
Saleh held cordial and friendly talks with Chinese President
Jiang Zemin, and joined in separate meetings with Qiao Shi,
chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC) Standing
Committee, and Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
(CPPCC). Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen
also held talks with his Yemeni counterpart Dr. Abdul Karim Al
Iryani.
</P>
<P>
The communique stressed that friendly bilateral ties and
cooperative relations between the two nations have withstood the
changing international situation since the establishment of
diplomatic relations more than 40 years ago, and in so doing have
set a fine example for handling relations between developing
countries.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from the two nations discussed ways to further advance
in a comprehensive way bilateral relations and agreed that there
is a relatively high complementarity in their economic spheres,
according to the communique. It also noted that the Chinese and
Yemeni leaders are prepared to further expand cooperation in
wide-ranging areas, including trade, energy, science, technology,
health and education.
</P>
<P>
The leaders will encourage companies, businesses and
entrepreneurs from their respective nations to engage in various
forms of fruitful, mutual cooperation to benefit the two peoples.
</P>
</TEXT>
