<HEADLINE> China, Yemen Sign Joint Press Communique (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With regard to the Middle East peace process, the communique
said the two countries agreed that the concerned parties should
conclude a comprehensive, just and lasting peace on the basis of
the relevant United Nations resolutions (UN) and the principle of
"land for peace".
</P>
<P>
Both sides expressed deep concern about the crisis over
weapons inspections in Iraq and about the continuing deterioration
in the situation. The communique noted the difficulties
surrounding the use of force to resolve the issue and stressed
that peaceful means should be used to end the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The leaders called on Iraq to implement the relevant UN
Security Council resolutions in all-round way, fully cooperate
with the UN Special Commission and conscientiously fulfill its
obligations. The communique said the two countries support all
efforts to resolve the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the two sides expressed their willingness to make
common efforts in establishing a just and reasonable new
international political and economic order.
</P>
<P>
President Saleh expressed his admirations for China's
tremendous achievements in reform and opening-up, and extended
gratitude for the warm welcome and hospitality offered by the
Chinese government and people. Chinese President Jiang Zemin also
expressed his appreciations for Yemen's efforts to realize
national unity and stability, and its success in economic and
administrative reform.
</P>
<P>
