<HEADLINE> Curfew Remains in Areas of Two Indian States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 19 (Xinhua) -- A curfew in some areas of
Uttar Pradesh and Rajasthan states remained in force Thursday as
the situation there was still tense.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said Ferozabad city in Uttar Pradesh is
still under curfew and security forces kept vigil at the Imambara
locality where members of two communities exchanged fire
Wednesday, wounding at least 10 people, three of them seriously.
</P>
<P>
Forty people have been taken into custody in connection with
Wednesday's clash which followed an altercation between two bangle
dealers. Seven bangle shops were set on fire.
</P>
<P>
The indefinite curfew, which was imposed in two areas of Ajmer
town in Rajasthan State after group clashes on Tuesday, remained
in force for the third day Thursday. The trouble started over a
dispute on photographing some pilgrims. Violent groups resorted to
stone-pelting and someone reportedly opened fire from the mob.
They also set afire more than a dozen shops.
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times said in an editorial entitled "a Tense
Poll" Thursday, "One reason for the prevailing tension is perhaps
the closeness of the contests. As a result, the usual appeals on
the basis of caste and community may have become even more
intense." 
</P>
