<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Controls Total Number of Transient Laborers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will limit the total
number of transient laborers to around 1.3 million during 1998,
according to a recent regulation issued by the municipal government.
</P>
<P>
City officials explained that the regulation is designed to
relieve tension on the city's transportation system and other
infrastructure facilities.
</P>
<P>
The financial, insurance and post and telecommunications
sectors should limit the employment of transit laborers, the
regulation says.
</P>
<P>
The regulation requires the city's service sector and other
enterprises to provide at least 50 percent of job opportunities to
local laidoff workers and unemployed people.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that Beijing had 170,000 laid-off workers
and unemployed people in 1997, some 80 percent of whom have
found reemployment through various channels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
