<HEADLINE> HK Business Community Welcomes First SAR Budget (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dr. Victor Fung Kwok-king, chairman of the Trade Development
Council, said that through a package of very specific budgetary
measures, the Financial Secretary has sent a strong message to the
international business community that Hong Kong is determined to
remain competitive.
</P>
<P>
He said he is confident the overall budget strategy will help
to sustain the momentum of the SAR's economic growth through this
challenging period.
</P>
<P>
Fung said that the Financial Secretary had rightly pinpointed
two key factors for Hong Kong's continued trade growth -- the
expansion and stability of the Chinese mainland economy and the
strength of the U.S. market.
</P>
<P>
"These are markets where the TDC is particularly active with
its promotions this year," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Tourist Association also welcomed the measures
proposed by the Tsang in his Budget speech.
</P>
<P>
The measures include the cutting of the airport departure tax
from 100 HK dollars (12.8 U.S. dollars) to 50 HK dollars (6.4 U.S.
dollars) when the new airport opens, the reduction of the hotel
room tax from 5 percent to 3 percent, and the bringing down of the
Marine Ferry Terminal Passenger Fee from 25 HK dollars (3.2 U.S.
dollars) to 18 HK dollars (2.3 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
"All these measures will give the community new confidence in
the future of tourism," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong General Chamber of Commerce believed that the
first SAR Budget provides a sound base for the economic recovery
of Hong Kong without abandoning its long history of fiscal
prudence.
</P>
<P>
The Budget also shows that Hong Kong has a very healthy economy
attractive for investment and has a very strong ability to benefit
its people, it said.
</P>
<P>
Stanley Ko, chairman of the Hong Kong Coalition of Service
Industries, also warmly welcomed the Budget, saying: "the
Financial Secretary has achieved the difficult task of balancing
the need for prudence on the one hand, and answering the call of
the community for financial relief on the other."
</P>
<P>
"The reduction in hotel tax and airport tax will together
inject a healthy dose to our troubled tourism sector," he said.
</P>
