<HEADLINE> Late Premier's Birth Anniversary Marked in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Authors of a book on the late
Chinese Premier Zhou Enlai and his life in Beijing today gathered
together here to mark the centenary of Zhou's birth.
</P>
<P>
The authors and others who had known Zhou Enlai recollected his
outstanding leadership and noble character.
</P>
<P>
The book named "Zhou Enlai and Beijing" was a collection of
articles by 76 authors on his concern and instructions over
Beijing's development and his friendship with the public figures
of various sectors who lived in the city.
</P>
<P>
Commemorative activities about the late premier, one of the
most revered figures in modern China, has swept the nation as the
centenary of his birth on March 5, 1898 approaches.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Enlai (March 5, 1898 - January 8, 1976) served as China's
premier from 1949 when the People's Republic of China was founded
till his death.  
