<HEADLINE> FIFA Gives Ultimatum to Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The Federation of Football
Association (FIFA) has warned Nigeria to put all necessary
facilities in place by the end of May, otherwise it will lose the
chance to host the 1999 Under-20 FIFA World Youth Championship.
</P>
<P>
The world football governing body's ultimatum was received
Wednesday by the Nigeria Football Association in Abuja, local
media said.
</P>
<P>
To make its threat real, FIFA has put Argentina on standby,
reports said.
</P>
<P>
FIFA officials led by Jamaican Jack Warner had expressed
dissatisfaction with the state of available facilities for the
competition when they visited Nigeria last December.
</P>
<P>
Of all the six designated venues, only three stadium in Lagos,
Ibadan and Enugu were given pass marks, while the the other three
in Kano, Calabar and Kaduna failed to get FIFA's nod.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the Nigerian government has constituted the Local
Organizing Committee and charged it with the task of getting all
the facilities ready for the championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
