<HEADLINE> Snow Hits Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has recorded its first
snowfall since January 28, the Chinese Lunar New Year's Day.
</P>
<P>
"Snow is very rare at this time of the year," said Niu Donglin,
an official from the Beijing Meteorological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Niu estimated that the maximum precipitation today would reach
13 millimeters.
</P>
<P>
Local officials noted that today's precipitation will benefit
crops in north China.
</P>
<P>
The snow will also cleanse the air and reduce cases of flu,
which has hit the city in recent months.
</P>
<P>
Many Beijing residents braved the sleet to purchase
commemorative stamps marking the first anniversary of Deng
Xiaoping's death. 
</P>
