<HEADLINE> Edmundo Leaves Fiorentina for Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Brazil striker Edmundo has left
Fiorentina for dispute with the Series A club and flew back home
on Thursday in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Edmundo left shortly after midnight after he threated earlier
to walk away if the Florence's club did not guarantee him a first
team place.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian was bought by Fiorentina from Vasco Da Gama of
Brazilian last May for 7.4 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
But he only played two games for his new club which lineups
Argentine captain Gabriel Batistuta plus another in attack.
</P>
<P>
And the other spot is battled by Belgian Lius Oliveira,
Domenico Morfeo and Anselmo Robbiati, alongside Edmundo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
