<HEADLINE> No Drought Predicted in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Drought will not occur in the
east part of southern Africa including Mozambique as a result of
the current El Nino phenomenon, local paper "Noticias" reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This forecast was made at a workshop on climate concluded here
Wednesday, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The workshop was sponsored by the Mozambican Ministry of
Environmental Coordination and the University of Columbia of the
United States to assess the predictions on climate made last
September which said central and southern Mozambique would be hit
by drought caused by El Nino from January to March this year.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican and foreign experts present at the workshop said
that indications show the west part of southern Africa rather
than its east part would be severely affected by drought.
</P>
</TEXT>
