<HEADLINE> China Ranks First in Eiderdown Production and Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- China exported feathers and
eiderdown products valued at 800 million US dollars in 1997, up
seven percent on 1996.
</P>
<P>
The nation currently leads the world in terms of production and
exports of eiderdown products.
</P>
<P>
Today's International Trade News reported that China
anticipates excellent opportunities to advance eiderdown
production over the next several decades.
</P>
<P>
Abundant feather resources have provided a solid foundation for
the growth of the down manufacturing industry, and an increasing
number of countries are importing feather and eiderdown products.
</P>
<P>
The consumption of feather products is also growing in China,
and the country is rapidly emerging as one of the world's major
consumers of eiderdown products, according to the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
China adopted a guarantee hallmark system for eiderdown
products in October 1995 in order to ensure sound development of
the industry. Some 41 eiderdown products manufactured in 18
provinces and autonomous regions have been granted rights to use
the mark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
