<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Takes Steps to Expand Navy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
taken massive steps for the development of the armed forces along
with the country's socioeconomic development, national English
newspapers reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina while
addressing a function marking the commissioning of a maritime
surveillance and coastal patrol craft of the Bangladesh Navy
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We have taken steps for the expansion, development and
modernization of the Navy like the Army and Air Force," the prime
minister said.
</P>
<P>
She said necessary formalities to procure a frigate for the
Bangladesh Navy have been completed. "The frigate will be added to
the naval fleet soon."
</P>
<P>
"We are sincerely trying to buy maritime patrol aircraft and
helicopters for the Navy," she said, adding that the process is
under way for procuring modern equipment and vessels for the Navy
to increase its activities in hydrography and oceanography.
</P>
<P>
She further said some other development projects for the Navy
are under active consideration of the government. "We are trying
to strengthen our Navy despite the resources constraint."
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the reasons for this, she said the Navy has a great
role to play in utilizing the possibilities offered by maritime
resources and routes and the country has a large maritime boundary
and huge resources in the sea.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister added that apart from the fish resources,
the Bay of Bengal has a good reserve of gas and there are
prospects of oil and other mineral resources in the bay.
</P>
<P>
"So, the necessity of a strong modern and skilled Navy is
indispensable to ensure the security of our maritime boundary and
to conserve and collect the resources of exclusive economic zone,"
she stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
