<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Shootout in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Two persons were killed and two
others wounded in a running gunfight between a group of policemen
and a holdup suspect in Manila Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
The shootout began when an armed man allegedly held up a
taxicab and was later cornered near an intersection by policemen,
police said.
</P>
<P>
Moments later, the suspect managed to commandeer another
vehicle and escaped but he was stopped by a police mobile unit.
</P>
<P>
The man refused to yield and instead fired at his pursuers,
resulting in the killing of a female bystander. Finally, the
suspect himself was shot dead by police.
</P>
<P>
Two policemen were also wounded during the shootout.
</P>
<P>
The police have dispatched a team to trace the real identity of
the slain suspect.  
</P>
</TEXT>
