<HEADLINE> Uganda Ready for Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has decided to start
municipal, county and sub-county elections on March 7, a local
report said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Hajji Aziz Kasujja, chairman of the Uganda Electoral
Commission, was quoted as saying that they decided the
chairpersons on sub-county level will be elected on March 7 by
secret ballot.
</P>
<P>
Polls for the 13 municipalities countrywide will be held by
secret ballot on March 14, he added.
</P>
<P>
There will be no holidays on the voting days.
</P>
<P>
Kasujja said ballot papers for about 9 million registered
voters have arrived in the country and that the commission will
also issue new voter cards to all registered voters.
</P>
<P>
The voter cards distribution exercise will start from February
23 to March 5, the report quoted the chairman as saying.
</P>
<P>
In November 1996, the country's central government announced
that the local government elections were to be held between March
and April 1997, but they were postponed several times due to the
lack of election fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
