<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman Addresses Sino-EU Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao made the remarks
today during a regularly scheduled press conference when asked to
comment on prospects for Sino-EU relations.
</P>
<P>
Leon Brittan, vice-president of the European Commission, is
currently visiting China.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China and the EU, two major forces in the
international political and economic arena, share extensive common
interests in maintaining world peace and stability, and improving
common economic development.
</P>
<P>
Developing mutually beneficial long-term cooperative ties
between the two sides will not only be in the best interests of
the parties concerned, but will also promote Asian-European
cooperation, as well as world peace, stability and prosperity,
said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to its relations with the EU,
said Zhu. He pointed to the sound momentum in the constant
development of Sino-EU ties, and the marked results of expanded
cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The noted the positive significance of the EU proposal for
meetings between Chinese and EU leaders during the Asian-European
meeting scheduled for April.
</P>
<P>
China is ready to further enhance cooperation and contacts with
the EU in order to raise bilateral ties to a new plateau, the
spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
