<HEADLINE> Private Enterprises Thrive in Coastal Province of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang, an economically
developed coastal province in east China, has 90,000 private
enterprises with a combined registered capital of 47 billion yuan,
ranking second in China next to south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Private enterprises in Hangzhou, the provincial capital, grew
by 40.2 percent last year, the overseas edition of Beijing-based
"People's Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises have employed 1.35 million workers.
</P>
<P>
The private firms in Yongkang City have invested 188 million
yuan in importing 88 up-to-date sets of equipment, employing 110
experts and purchasing 230 items of technology. As a result, 40
new products have been developed and introduced into the
market. Twelve high-tech products have obtained state
certificates.  
</P>
</TEXT>
