<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Get Investment in Platinum Mine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
HARARE, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Anglo-American Corporation in
South Africa Wednesday announced plans to invest some 80 million
U.S. Dollars in a platinum mine in the midlands town of Shurugwi
in central Zimbabwe#,wnich is expected to create 1,400 jobs.
</P>
<P>
The Unki mine would be the second major platinum mine in
Zimbabwe after the Hartely platinum mine being developed by BHP
Minerals and Delta Gold from Australia in Chegutu, 80 kilometers
southwest of Harare.
</P>
<P>
Anglo Chief Executive Philip Baum said the mine would earn
Zimbabwe 880 million U.S. Dollars in foreign currency over its
life time.
</P>
<P>
The mine would have an initial life span of 20 years,
although Baum said extensive ore reserves surrounding it should
allow the span to be extended considerably as well as to increase
output.
</P>
<P>
The mine will produce 1.02 million tons of platinum ore per
annum when in full production it will be just below half the full
capacity of the Hartely mine, which is the second largest
platinum mine in the world.
</P>
<P>
Feasibility studies for the project which began in 1995 were
completed in October last year, while the construction of the
mine was expected to last two and half years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
