<HEADLINE> U.N. Opens Meeting of Industry, Technology Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The preparatory meeting for a
ministerial meeting on industrial and technological cooperation
was inaugurated Thursday at the Center of the U.N. Economic and
Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP) here.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from more than 40 countries and organizations
attended the opening ceremony of the preparatory senior officials
meeting presided over by Thai Industry Minister Somsak Thepsutin.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Somsak reviewed the economic turmoil in the
Southeast Asian region, saying the domino effect of local
currencies devaluation triggered by the sharp fall of the baht,
the Thai currency, should be attributed to the more and more
integrated world economy.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he called for increased contact and communication
and broadened cooperation within and beyond the region.
</P>
<P>
Before Somsak's speech, Adrianus Mooy, ESCAP executive
secretary, also made a statement, in which he noted that
challenges and opportunities lie ahead in achieving sustainable
industrial and technological development in the region.
</P>
<P>
The ministerial meeting will be held on Monday and Tuesday,
during which ministers are expected to discuss industrial and
technological restructuring, investment-related technology
transfer and other issues.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a separate symposium on the private sector's role in
the industrial and technological field will be held on February
21.
</P>
<P>
At the end of their meeting, the ministers are expected to
issue a declaration and an action plan suggesting measures for
further industrial and technological development.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of industry and technology ministers has been
organized periodically by the ESCAP, with the last meeting held in
Tehran, Iran, in June 1992.  
</P>
</TEXT>
