<HEADLINE> "Zhou Enlai and Beijing" Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The Central Literature
Publishing House released a new book entitled "Zhou Enlai and
Beijing" today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The work, which includes 72 articles containing 400,000 Chinese
characters, provides vivid descriptions of Zhou's instructions
related to industrial and agricultural production, the
construction of urban infrastructure, public security, education,
cultural progress and the living standards of people living in the
Chinese capital. The book clearly reveals Zhou's great concern for
people from various circles in Beijing.
</P>
