<HEADLINE> UNHCR Arranges Repatriation of Refugees in W. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The United Nation High
Commission for Refugees (UNHCR) is making arrangement to
repatriate Congolese refugees in western Uganda, a high official
of UNHCR has said here.
</P>
<P>
Sadako Ogata, the U.N. high commissioner for refugees, told a
news conference Wednesday that a team has been sent to the
Democratic Republic of Congo for the purpose.
</P>
<P>
She had talks with Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni on the
same day on the refugee issue, Ogata said.
</P>
<P>
"The president made it clear that people must go back to their
countries voluntarily," Ogata narrated.
</P>
<P>
The refugees reached western Uganda last year when Laurent
Kabila's troops launched their attacks to grip power.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR cannot influence political situation in a country, but
it will help in dealing with the problem, Ogata added.
</P>
<P>
She had an impression that the period of large outflows of
refugees in this region has subsided, Ogata added.
</P>
<P>
Ogata began her three-day trip to Uganda from February 17. She
is visiting nine African countries including Zimbabwe, Tanzania,
Burundi, Rwanda, Kenya, Uganda, Ethiopia, the Republic of Congo
and Democratic Republic of Congo, exploring ways to enhance
adherence to humanitarian principles and refugee law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
