<HEADLINE> Portugal, African States to Discuss Coalition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Defense ministers from
Portugal and five Portuguese-speaking African countries will
gather in Lisbon, capital of Portugal in July to decide on the
establishment of a coalition force of these countries.
</P>
<P>
The idea of setting up a coalition force of
Portuguese-speaking countries, initiated by Antonio Vitorino,
former defense minister of Portugal, last year when he visited
Angola and Mozambique, was welcomed by the African countries.
</P>
<P>
According to Angola News Agency Thursday, the proposed
coalition force was aimed at carrying out a peace keeping mission
in Africa in line with U.N. and OAU decisions to ensure stability
and peace in the continent, especially in Portuguese-speaking
African countries.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the establishment of a coalition force
was also aimed to promote cooperation between Portugal and five
Portuguese-speaking African countries.
</P>
<P>
