<HEADLINE> Chinese Municipality to Link with Japan by Air </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- China Southwestern Airlines
will open an air route from Chongqing, a new municipality in
southwest China, to Nagoya in Japan on March 30.
</P>
<P>
It is the first international regular air route for Chongqing
after it became China's fourth municipality in 1997 and is now the
only direct route to Japan from southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The Boeing 757 jet will fly two weekly return flights, on
Mondays and Thursdays, with each leg requiring a flight time of
about four hours, according to sources from the airlines.
</P>
<P>
Japan is an important trading partner with the municipality. A
dozen Japanese companies cooperate with enterprises in Chongqing in
producing motor vehicles and cars, using some 300 million US
dollars from Japan. Currently, two Japanese banks have set up
their representative offices in Chongqing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
