<HEADLINE> Books on Deng Xiaoping Popular Among Beijing Readers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- "I worship and love Deng
Xiaoping, and I felt so sad over his death last year," a
university student told reporters while reading a biography of
Deng in a local bookstore, SDX Joint Publishing Company.
</P>
<P>
"It is his reform and opening-up policies that made China
stronger," said the student named Yang Chengwei, who is majored in
economic management.
</P>
<P>
Nearly all the readers who have come to the bookstore recently
are buying books on Deng Xiaoping, who died on Feburary 19, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The bookstore has opened three special counters for books on
Deng, and sells 70-to-100 copies daily. The bookstore has sold
more than 10,000 books concerning the late leader during the past
year.
</P>
<P>
At present, some 100 different books on the late leader are
being sold around the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
One of these books, "My Father Deng Xiaoping" written by his
daughter Xiao Rong (Mao Mao), is most popular among local readers.
</P>
<P>
Some scholars attributed the popularity of books on Deng to the
his theory and charisma. 
</P>
