<HEADLINE> Timmer Wins Women's 1,000m Speed Skating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Marianne Timmer of the
Netherlands claimed her second gold medal in speed skating at the 18th
Olympic Winter Games when she won the 1,000m race on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch skater, surprising winner in the 1,500m on Monday,
sprinted to cross the finish line at a new Olympic record time of one
minute and 16.51 seconds, beating the 10-year-old mark set by Christa
Rothenburger of Germany at the Calgary games.
</P>
<P>
She pushed world record holder and pre-favourite Christine Witty of
the United States into the second place, with a clocking of one minute
and 16.79 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Catriona Lemay-Doan of Canada managed to finish third at 1:17.37.
</P>
<P>
With Timmer's victory, Dutch skaters have collected five gold
medals from speed skating, with Gianni Romme winning the men's 5,000m
and 10,000m, Ids Postma men's 1,000m.
</P>
<P>
Germany's strongest skater Franziska Schenk, who was paired with
Timmer, crashed on the second curve and did not finish the race.
</P>
</TEXT>
