<HEADLINE> Harare to Construct Major Dam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 19 (Xinhua) -- A new major dam, Kunzwi in
Murewa, will cost the Harare City Council more than five billion
Zimbabwean Dollars or 300 million U.S. Dollars, "The Herald"
daily reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Kunzwi Dam will be built on the Nyagui river, and it will have
a crest 2.6 km long and be 40.3 m high. The resultant lake will
cover 986 hectares and should yield 70 million cubic meters of
water a year from the total capacity of 157.9 million cubic
meters.
</P>
<P>
The water in Kunzwi will be considerably clearer than the
polluted contents of Lake Chivero and Lake Manyame, the two major
storage dams now serving the city.
</P>
<P>
Tender documents for Kunzwi have been ready since October last
year, although no invitations to tender have yet been made by the
council.
</P>
<P>
Apart from several local financing institutions, the African
Development Bank and a Japanese organization are also interested
in the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
