<HEADLINE> China's Anhui Province Launches Poverty Reduction Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, February 19 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province
recently launched a poverty reduction project with the aid of
overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
The comprehensive agricultural development project in the
southwest part of Anhui is expected to benefit more than 500,000
poverty-stricken people in Huoshan, Yuexi, Qianshan and two other
poor counties.
</P>
<P>
The project involves an investment of 540 million yuan,
including 26.53 million U.S. dollars in international loans. The
World Food Program has provided 14,000 tons of grain.
</P>
<P>
The project focuses on improving farming conditions, boosting
grain and fishery production, and getting dropouts to return to
school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
