<HEADLINE> Maier Wins Second Gold at Nagano Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Hermann Maier of Austria
claimed his second gold medal at the 18th Olympic Winter Games when he
won the men's giant slalom on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ex-bricklayer, who was badly crashed in the men's downhill but
followed to win the super giant slalom, was clocked two minutes and
38.51 seconds for the gold. His teammate Stefan Eberharter was second
at 2:39.36 and Michael Von Gruenigen of Switzerland finished third at
2:39.69.
</P>
<P>
Maier, the most prominent Alpine skiier at present, was quite happy
for his second gold in the Olympics. "I am so happy, and sorry about
my downhill. but I am so happy with two medals, it is wonderful," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian, who is making his deput at winter Olympics, had
challenged much difficulties before being acknowledged by the Austrian
team.
</P>
<P>
Italian Alpine skiing legend Alberto Tomba's efforts to win an
Olympic gold was smashed in a few minutes. After starting from the
first gate, he crashed and did not finish the first run. 
</P>
</TEXT>
