<HEADLINE> China Selects Top 50 Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Beijing becomes the second of
the top 50 Chinese cities selected in terms of overall social and
economic strength, today's Beijing Youth Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
According to a study of 219 cities at or above the prefectural
levels conducted by the urban social and economic investigation
team under the State Statistical Bureau, Shanghai comes the first
and is followed by Beijing, Guangzhou and Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The top four cities are playing a leading role in China's
political, economic and cultural development, the study finds.
</P>
<P>
Overall strength refers to the advanced degree in politics,
economy, social development, infrastructure, environment
protection, science and technology, and culture and education.
</P>
<P>
The study also shows that three regions, the area in the Bohai
Bay, the Yangtze River Delta and Pearl River Delta, where over 40
cities at or above the prefectural levels are located, have the
fastest economic growth and social progress in the country, and
are the vigorous forces for the country's growth of national
economy.
</P>
<P>
The study also reveals some problems such as the imbalanced
development between different cities and gaps between in the
eastern and western parts of the country as well as poor urban
environment and infrastructures facilities in some of the cities.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
