<HEADLINE> East China Province to Build Five Expressways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, February 19 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
will speed up construction of transport facilities by completing
five expressways totaling 1,228 kilometers by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The economically developed province plans to invest an
estimated 43 billion yuan (5.18 billion US dollars) in this
ambitious project which will be done in three phases, said Tang
Hanqing, director of the provincial communications department.
</P>
<P>
The five high-grade roads, linking Fujian's nine cities and
prefectures, are Fuzhou-Xiamen-Zhangzhou expressway,
Zhangzhou-Zhao'an expressway, Zhangzhou-Longyan expressway,
Fuzhou-Fuding expressway and Fujian section of the Beijing-Fuzhou
expressway.
</P>
<P>
"These facilities are expected to further boost the economic
growth in Fujian," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
The coastal province had 84 kilometers of expressway in
operation by the end of 1997. It put two billion yuan in highway
construction in the year and plans to invest another 1.6 billion
yuan this year. 
