<HEADLINE> Experts Say China Should Develop Precious Stones Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- China has broad prospects in
the development of precious stones and a greater effort should
be made in finding them, a recent forum on precious stones was
told.
</P>
<P>
Experts said at the forum that the precious stone market in
China needs to be standardized.
</P>
<P>
The number of businesses making jewelry and similar items in
China has gone from 120 in 1978, when the country started opening
to the outside world, to some 10,000 now. China exported 1.2
billion U.S. dollars worth of jewelry last year.
</P>
<P>
They say that China has good geological conditions for
precious stones and geologists have in recent years
made an effort to look for them and have reported encouraging
finds in Qinghai, Xinjiang, and Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
However, many precious stones are still buried beneath the
surface of the earth, and increased prospecting is urgently
needed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
