<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Back From Three-Nation Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng wound
up a successful official goodwill visit to Luxembourg, Netherlands
and Russia, and returned here by a special plane earlier today.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Russia, Li attended the third regular
meeting between the premiers of China and Russia.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing and his wife, who have attended the
annual meeting of the World Economic Forum in Davos and visited
Switzerland, Spain, Belgium, Denmark, and the European Union
headquarters, and accompanied Premier Li's participation in the
meeting in Russia, returned aboard the same plane.
</P>
<P>
Among those who met Premier Li and his party at the Great Hall
of People were Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji, Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qi Qichen, Lei Jieqiong, vice-chairwoman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress, Luo Gan, a state
councillor and secretary-general of the State Council, Wan
Guoquan, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, and Wu Yi, minister of
the Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, as well as diplomatic
envoys from these countries and the EU.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li's entourage, including Cao Gangchuan, minister in
charge of the Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for
National Defence, Liu Huaqiu, director of the Foreign Affairs
Office under the State Council, and Lu Ruihua, governor of
Guangdong Province, returned to Beijing with Premier Li.
</P>
<P>
Among those who saw Premier Li off in Moscow includes Russian
First Deputy Prime Minister Nemtsov and other Russian officials as
well as Li Fenglin, Chinese ambassador to Russia. Li reviewed a
guard of honor of three services in company of Nemtsov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
