<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Austria Says Europe Will Have More Confidence in Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Prime Minister Viktor
Klima has said that Europe will have more confidence in its
economy and foreign economic policy.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release by the Social Democratic Party of
Austria on Wednesday, Klima told an American business council in
Vienna that Europe will gradually pursue a common security and
defense policy.
</P>
<P>
"There will be a policy that can better coordinate the exchange
rates of the dollar, yen and the European currency," he said. "The
European currency has the prospect of becoming one that can be
used for world trade and foregin reserves."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the economic and currency union will
definitely lead to coordinated financial, economic and social
policies of Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
