<HEADLINE> ADB to provide 280 Million Dollar Aid to Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 19 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
will provide Bangladesh with 280 million U.S. dollars for
financing five new projects in 1998 besides continuation of 36
ongoing projects in the country, the independent United News of
Bangladesh (UNB) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by ADB's Director of Programs Geert van der
Linden in Dhaka Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
The five projects are rural credit (43 million dollars),
development of environment in the Sundarbands (40 million
dollars), fourth natural gas (100 million dollars), upgradation of
Chittagong port (80 million dollars), and poverty reduction in
Dhaka city (17 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Besides, the ADB official said that the bank would consider
providing 100 million dollars for a 10th power project in view of
acute shortage of electricity in Bangladesh. 
</P>
