<HEADLINE> Myanmar Famous Writer Mya Than Tint Passes Away </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 19 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar famous writer and
translator Mya Than Tint passed away at the Yangon General
Hospital here Wednesday night at the age of 69, according to an
obituary of the bereaved family here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mya Than Tint translated numerous noted foreign literature
works into Myanmar language when he was alive such as Russia's
"War and Peace", America's "Gone with the Wind", China's "A Dream
of Red Mansions", "Storm" and "Teahouse".
</P>
<P>
Of these, the translation work of "A Dream of Red Mansions"
into Myanmar language with a book in nine volumes of 3,500 pages
was completed in late 1980s, becoming the longest
foreign-translated work published in the country.
</P>
<P>
Due to his noted achievements in the field, the late Mya Than
Tint was awarded by the state with Sarpay Beikman prize in foreign
literature translation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
