<HEADLINE> Panama, Uruguay Sign Three Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Panama and Uruguay signed
three agreements Wednesday to promote investment and technological
cooperation and develop air services.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were aimed at creating and maintaining favorable
conditions for investment in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The governments said it was necessary to promote and protect
foreign investment and support economic prosperity in Panama and
Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
The agreements stipulate that their airlines will have the
right to overfly each country's territory and make non-commercial
flights, carrying and offloading passengers and mail services.
</P>
<P>
The technological cooperation agreement would include the
exchange of experts, equipment and materials, professional
training and the creation of research institutions.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by the two foreign ministers during
a visit by Uruguayan President Julio Maria Sanguinetti to Panama.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sanguinetti and his Panamanian counterpart, Ernesto
Perez Balladares, signed a joint declaration Wednesday to
eradicate poverty and develop democracy.
</P>
<P>
Sanguinetti arrived Tuesday for a two-day visit and he will go
on to Colombia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
