<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 19 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province has set 1998 price control goals calling for the growth
rate in the retail price index to remain below three percent, and
the consumer price index at less than five percent.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Governor Tang Bingquan said the provincial government
will extend great effort to realize the goals.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's retail price index rose only 0.1 percent in 1997,
with the consumer index growing by 1.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Tang called on government departments at various levels to
continue implementing relatively stringent fiscal and monetary
policies in order to curb inflation.
</P>
<P>
He also urged local governments to take effective measures to
improve the responsibility system so as to ensure realization of
price control goals and steady operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
