<HEADLINE> Korda Beats Portas in EC Tennis Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 18 (Xinhua) -- World number two Petr Korda
of Czech Republic fought off illness and Spaniard Albert Portas to
win 7-5, 6-2 in the second round of the European Community tennis
championship in Antwerp, Belgium, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Korda, the top seed here, requested medical assistance in the
first set and interrupted the match for several minutes before
resuming play.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Open champion was helped by a series of unforced
errors by Portas, and finally got into his stride in the second
set.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Britain's Tim Henman crashed out in the first
round when he lost 7-5, 6-3 to unseeded Swede Magnus Norman.
</P>
<P>
Britain's number one Greg Rusedski, the fifth seed, beat
Moroccan rising star Hicham Arazi 7-6, 3-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed Russian Yevgeny Kafelnikov celebrated his birthday
with a 7-5, 5-7, 6-3 victory against Czech Jiri Novak.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Marc Rosset of Switzerland rallied from the
brink of defeat to beat Australian Open quarter-finalist Nicolas
Kiefer of Germany 7-6, 4-6, 7-6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
