<HEADLINE> Germany Beats Oman in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Germany scored an easy 2-0
win over Oman in a soccer friendly in Muscat, Oman, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Germans, which dominated the game from the start, opened
the scoring in the 26th minute through captain Jurgen Kohler, who
netted from a corner kick from Thomas Hessler.
</P>
<P>
Joerg Heinrich scored through a similiar action when he
deflected another corner from Hessler in the 61st minute.
</P>
<P>
The German team was without injured striker Jurgen Klinsmann
and some Bayern Munich players who stayed at home for a German Cup
semifinal.
</P>
<P>
The Munich players will join the squad for a friendly against
Saudi Arabia on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Germans will be in the same group with Iran, Yugoslavia and
the United States in the World Cup finals in June. 
