<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgian Grand Prix Saved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Formula One's ruling body FIA
confirmed on Wednesday that this year's Belgian Grand Prix will be
saved as scheduled on August 30.
</P>
<P>
The race, one of the most famous in Europe, had appeared doomed
last week when a Belgian appeal court upheld a law that will
introduce a strict ban on all forms of tobacco advertising and
sponsorship from next year.
</P>
<P>
FIA had warned in January that this year's race would be
cancelled unless an exemption for Formula One was agreed by
February 15.
</P>
<P>
Cars will apparently be free to carry tobacco logos at this
year's race, until the introduction of the new law next year.
</P>
<P>
China and South Africa have been hoping to replace Belgium to
stage the race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
