<HEADLINE> Ambassador Qin: China Favors Diplomatic Solution to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 18 (xinhua) -- A peaceful and
diplomatic solution to the current crisis over the United Nations
weapons inspection in Iraq is what the whole international
community has expected, Chinese Permanent Representative to the
United Nations Qin Huasun stressed here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting of the security Council, Qin Huasun
said UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan made a wise decision to make
a mediation trip to Baghdad at this critical moment, and China
hopes that his mission to Baghdad would help to resolve the
current crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Ambassador said China fully supports the UN chief's visit
to Iraq and wishes him success.
</P>
<P>
Qin reiterated China's consistent position on the issue of
Iraq, saying that Iraq should fully comply with all the relevant
resolutions of the Security Council and cooperate fully with the
United Nations Special Commission in charge of dismantling Iraq's
weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Qin stresses the sovereignty, dignity and
territorial integrity of Iraq should be fully respected.
</P>
<P>
Qin expressed the hope that all parties concerned should avoid
all actions that would not help to defuse the current crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
