<HEADLINE> Dow Closes at Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Led by technology shares,
U.S. stocks remained bullish for the sixth consecutive session on
Wednesday with the Dow Jones industrial average jumping 52.56
points to close at 8,451.06.
</P>
<P>
The Dow's achievement is not only a new record close, but also
the first time the benchmark barometer crossed over the 8,400
line.
</P>
<P>
It is nearly 6.9 percent higher than the Dow's level at the
beginning of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Broader market indicators also showed gains today.
</P>
<P>
On the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE), advancing issues beat
decliners 7-5 with 1,704 up, 1,196 down and 577 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Trading volume rose to 604.81 million shares from 598.07
million shares on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 stock list gained 9.30 to 1,032.06
and the NYSE composite index rose 4.44 to 537.23.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nastaq composite index, which declined
yesterday, rebounded today by gaining 12.31 points and closing at
1,715.74.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies advanced 1.50 to
454.69 and the small company dominated American Stock Exchange
composite index rose 1.07 to 688.50.  
</P>
</TEXT>
