<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Cambodia Urban Water Supply Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank announced
Wednesday the approval of a credit equivalent to some 30.96
million U.S. dollars for an urban water supply project in
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
This project will enhance drinking water availability and
quality in Cambodia's two largest cities on the basis of effective
demand, improve the water utilities' technical and economic
performance, widen the availability of non-drinking water for
commercial and industrial usage so as to boost economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association, the World Bank's concessionary lending
wing for developing countries. 
