<HEADLINE> Five Telecommunication Satellites Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 18 (Xinhua) -- A Boeing Delta II rocket
carrying five telecommunication satellites was successfully
launched into space at 5:58 (PST) Wednesday morning from
Vandenberg Air Force Base, California.
</P>
<P>
The five satellites are part of a space-based
telecommunications network planned by Iridium. The network,
composing of 66 satellites, already has 51 satellites in orbit and
will provide wireless handheld telephone services from almost any
place on Earth.
</P>
<P>
The Iridium network is scheduled to be working later this year.
</P>
